		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philad.</placeName> <date>July 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5620</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Miss Rosa Mordecai</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Watervliet Arsenal NB.</placeName></p>
				<p>My dear Friend.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your very refreshing note was received<lb/> about an hour ago&#44; and I assure you that it almost compliments<lb/> me for so much suffering as I had been sure&#44;<lb/> to have so many kind inquiries made by my<lb/> friends&#44; you &#38; yours included.  I today sat up for<lb/> the first time to write at a table since my<lb/> last yesterday two weeks <add>&#63;</add> and I trust that<lb/> by middle of next week I shall be <add>&#63;</add><lb/> more to be out.  But I am admonished by the<lb/> <add>&#63;</add>tant pain whenever <add>&#63;</add>&#44; that it will<lb/> be a long while before I shall be exempt from<lb/> the consequences of an accident as painful as<lb/> unlooked for.  <persName>Jones I Horace</persName> <add>&#63;</add> last evening&#44;<lb/> in my bed <add>&#63;</add>.  I am indebted to him for his constant<lb/> inquiries.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The house is emptied of all its inhabitants<lb/> some of servants&#59; and how pleased would I<lb/> be to have you here for an uninterrupted quarrel</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>on any given topic for though my back is<lb/> lamed&#44; my tongue is loose on the proper <add>&#63;</add>.<lb/> Only ladies have the privilege of a tongue<lb/> fastening in the middle&#59; we from miserable<lb/> masculiness must needs be <add>&#63;</add> well the<lb/> use of it in the front part.  But then we may<lb/> not try it then to the best advantage&#44; even<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> arguing the ladies.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My writing is hardly presu<add>&#63;</add> to a<lb/> lady&#59; than to <add>&#63;</add> almost straight up to make<lb/> <add>&#63;</add>&#44; and being near sighted with all&#44;<lb/> to not writing with spectacles&#44; than to trust<lb/> to my readiness in handling the pen to make<lb/> it figures as they come without having any hope<lb/> of offering a specimen of caligraphy.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Remember me to your parents and <add>&#63;</add>&#44;<lb/> &#38; return to bless <add>&#63;</add> my best thanks for<lb/> he<add>&#63;</add> joint kind inquiries.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Hoping that the course of your life<lb/> may run smooth without accident or<lb/> severe trials I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">truly your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName></p>
			<pb n="Envelope"/>
				<p><addressee>Miss Rosa Mordecai</addressee></p>
				<p>care of <persName>Major A. Mordecai</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Watervliet Arsenal</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>West Ferry</placeName></p>
